swatch: swatch (Simple WATCHdog)
swatch:
swatch: Swatch was originally written to actively monitor messages as
swatch: they are written to a log file via the UNIX syslog utility.
swatch: For a simple demonstration type "perl swatch
swatch: --examine=FILENAME" with FILENAME being the file that you
swatch: would like to see the contents of. All this example will do is
swatch: demonstrate the different text modes that are available with
swatch: to the echo action.
swatch:
